Olympic male cyclist of all time, will be carrying the British
flag at the opening ceremony of the London Olympics.  The 36-year-old Hoy, who has won four gold medals, will
mark his fourth Olympics by leading the British team into the
Olympic Stadium on July 27, Team GB said in an emailed statement
